<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Further_reading">Further reading</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Paradesi_Jews&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Further reading"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li>Diamonds and Coral: Anglo-Dutch Jews and Eighteenth-Century Trade New edition by Gedalia Yogev (Author)</li>
<li>Renascent Empire?: The House of Braganza and the Quest for Stability in Portuguese Monsoon Asia C.1640-1683 by Glenn Joseph Ames</li>
<li>Global Trade and Commercial Networks: Eighteenth-Century Diamond Merchants By Tijl Vanneste</li>
<li>Goods from the East, 1600-1800: Trading Eurasia By Felicia Gottmann, Hanna Hodacs, Chris Nierstrasz</li>
<li>The Jewish Merchant-Colony in Madras (Fort St. George) during the 17th and 18th Centuries: A Contribution to the Economic and Social History of the Jews in India (Concluded) Walter J. Fischel</li>
<li>The Palgrave Dictionary of Anglo-Jewish History edited by W. Rubinstein, Michael A. Jolles</li>
<li><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFHarikrishnan2008" class="citation news cs1">Harikrishnan, Charmy (23 November 2008). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://archive.indianexpress.com/news/the-last-tribe/388811/0">"The Last Tribe: A lament for the dying Jewry in Kerala"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/The_Indian_Express" title="The Indian Express">The Indian Express</a></i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">6 October</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Indian+Express&amp;rft.atitle=The+Last+Tribe%3A+A+lament+for+the+dying+Jewry+in+Kerala&amp;rft.date=2008-11-23&amp;rft.aulast=Harikrishnan&amp;rft.aufirst=Charmy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Farchive.indianexpress.com%2Fnews%2Fthe-last-tribe%2F388811%2F0&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AParadesi+Jews" class="Z3988"></span></li></ul>
